	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Nov 24th 10:59 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.95]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings Xvail Trueblade,<br><br>I am one drop away from my Fiery Defender (and a few Raids for turn-ins) so here's a recount of what I have completed so far.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is a first hand account (mostly) and paraphrased for brevity.<br><br>1) I received my ghoulbane...and this was before you could quest for it, so I killed the Paladin Frog in Guk to get it.<br><br>2) I completed my quest for the Soulfire Sword. This included the general running around that's required, along with slaying the Troll in Mistmoore for the hilt and killing Sir Lucan for the testament that you turn in to get the first Blade that eventually becomes the Soulfire blade when given to Brother Hayle in Splitpaw. Check Soulfire Quest...it's all outlined step by step.<br><br>3) A LLLOOOOOOOOOOOONNNNGGGGGG stagnant pause of nothingness for 20+ levels.<br><br>4) I received my frost book half from Gorenaire during a raid. Most people get this half of the Book of Scale from Vox in Permafrost, but Gorenaire drops it too, on occasion. I got lucky.<br><br>5) I received my burnt book half of the Book of Scale from Severilous.  Most people get this half from Lord Nagafen in Solusek B, but Severilous and Talendar drop it also.<br><br>*STEP 4 AND 5 ARE BY FAR THE MOST DIFFICULT PARTS OF THE OVERALL PALADIN EPIC QUEST...and you can't really continue until you have completed them.*<br><br>6) I took both book halves (burnt and frost) to the NPC Quest person outside the gates of Qeynos. If facing the gates from outside Qeynos, she is far left, outside the wall near some boxes.  I gave her both book halves and 1000 platinum pieces and she combined the book halves into the Book of Scale.<br><br>7) I took the combined Book of Scale to the Oracle on the island in the Ocean of Tears and he took it and gave me a phylactery with Miragul's soul in it in return.<br><br>8) I took the phylactery to the caves under Permafrost that can be found under the river in Everfrost. I had a high level Enchanter charm Lich Miragul and then I handed him the phylactery.  He was KoS to me and you can't give it to him while being attacked....hence the charming.  When I gave it to him, he spawned into the REAL Miragul, who is a level 53 Necromancer.  I then killed him, along with some considerable help from guild members.  I looted his Head and his Robe.  By the way, his FIRST attack was a 1500 pt life tap on me! So be ready for that!!<br><br>9) I now have all 4 pieces needed to get the Fiery Avenger (mini-epic sword) in the Plane of Air. <br><br>10) (Not done yet) I go to the Plane of Air, have someone give 500 plat to Dirkog Steelhands in the Quest Hall, which will cause Inte Akera to spawn on the 4th island.  I turn in the Ghoulbane and get the 1st blessing, turn in Soulfire to get the second blessing, then give him both blessings AND the robe and head of Miragul and TADA...the Fiery Avenger mini-epic.<br><br>11) I went to the Plane of Hate on a raid and killed a Thought Corrupter that dropped the Tainted Darksteel Breastplate.  I looted the BP, took it to Kaladim, did the short quest there to get a special gem from Jark in the Kaladim Mines, took the BP and the Gem to Erudin and gave them to a Paladin (Reklon Gnallen) there in the Paladin Guild and he "purified" the BP and gave it back to me. (First step done!)<br><br>11) I then gathered a party of guild members and killed Kirak Vil, a Dark Elf guard in Nektulos forest. He is a level 55ish Shadow Knight. He dropped the Tainted Darksteel Shield. I took the shield to Felwithe and gave it to Elia the Pure who "purified" it and gave it back to. No gem or other item needed. Just give her the shield and she gives it back purified. Simple as that. (Step Two Done)<br><br>12) (Not yet Complete) I need to kill the "Keeper of Tombs" who is DEEEEEEP in The Hole.  He is a level 51 ghost looking mob. Killing him is not the problem. Getting to him is the chore. If you can get to him, you can kill him. It will take a raid to do this.  Once killed, he will drop the Tainted Darksteel Sword.  I get it purified as well.<br><br>13) (Not yet Complete) Once all three pieces (BP, Shield and Sword) are purifed then I am ready to turn them in to Reklon Gnallen, the Paladin in Erudin.  He will give me a Crested Token and give me yet another Quest...the quest to release the fallen paladin, who's items I just found and had purified, and cleanse his soul.<br><br>14) (Not yet Complete) I take the Crested Token and the Fiery Avenger to the Plane of Fear. Yes...another raid required, obviously.  I find Irak Altil, give him the crested token, then give him the Fiery Avenger, and DUNDUNDUNDAAAAHHH...I get the Paladin Epic, the Fiery Defender Sword!!  <br><br>WOOHOOO, drinks for everyone!! Party TIME!!!<br><br>Naturally, there is a TON of faction work involved here as well and faction is CRITICAL so make sure you check factions ALWAYS!<br><br>Hope this helps. There is obviously more detail than I have spelled out here, but take a look at:<br><br>www.everlore.com/quests<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Cavalier<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
